Package remodel.meta

Class Transform

java.lang.Object
remodel.meta.Nominal
remodel.meta.Namespace<Rule>
remodel.meta.Transform
public class Transform
extends Namespace<Rule>
Transform denotes a named transformation defined within a ReMoDeL rule set. A Transform has a name, which is fixed after creation, and belongs to a named rule set. A Transform declares a number of Metamodels, in which the source and target Concepts are defined, and defines a number of transformation Rules. A Mapping rule has one source and one target. An Updating rule has the same source and target. A Merging rule has multiple sources and one target.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Anthony J H Simons

    • addMetamodel

      public void addMetamodel​(Metamodel metamodel)
      Adds a source or target Metamodel to this Transform's Metamodels. This Transform may refer to one or more Metamodels. The same Metamodel may be both a source and a target, but is only added once to this Transform.
      Parameters:
      metamodel - the Metamodel.

    • getMetamodels

      public java.util.List<Metamodel> getMetamodels()
      Returns all the Metamodels referenced by this Transform. Metamodels are returned in the order that they were loaded when reading this Transform. This method is used by TransformCompiler to access the Metamodels used by this Transform; and these may be recompiled.
      Returns:
      a list of referenced Metamodels.

    • getMetaRoles

      public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getMetaRoles()
      Returns all the role-names played by each Metamodel referenced by this Transform. This is a list of source and target role names. This is used by TransformWriter to write out the Metamodel declarations in the same order that they were read.
      Returns:
      a list of source and target role names.

    • findConcept

      public Concept findConcept​(java.lang.String type)
      Looks up the Concept associated with the given type. If the type is qualified by the name of its owning Metamodel, then look up the type in the corresponding local Metamodel used by this Transform. If the type is not qualified, look up the type in any Metamodel, in the order that these were loaded. This is not guaranteed to be correct! Only valid after this Transform has loaded the relevant Metamodels.
      Parameters:
      type - the type name of the sought Concept.
      Returns:
      the Concept corresponding to this type name.

    • findProperty

      public Property findProperty​(java.lang.String name)
      Looks up a Property by its name in the current context. By this point, the Property must be a locally defined Rule, if it exists.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the Property.
      Returns:
      the Rule with the specified name.
      Throws:
      SemanticError - if no such Rule can be found.
